main event: On April 27, 1969, a civilian reported a sighting of a luminous light resembling a star in Arcanum, Ohio.
interesting points: The observation lasted approximately 10 minutes., The light was described as bright and hovering with no discernible motion., The object appeared 1500 feet away and 60 feet high., There were no other witnesses reported at the time of the sighting., The report concluded with 'INSUFFICIENT DATA' indicating the lack of definitive evidence.
sighted object: a luminous light resembling a star
witness description: A civilian who reported seeing the object.
